<paragraph id="8BC636A1D175FFC7688A2E3BFD96FAB2" blockId="4.[166,1225,906,1349]" pageId="4" pageNumber="423">
The anatomical features and size of this femur are compatible with the similar bone of the 
<typeStatus id="54C28803D175FFC768832E1BFEC3FB73" box="[210,260,1130,1156]" pageId="4" pageNumber="423">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D22D175FFC769D22E1BFDCBFB73" authorityName="Mc Laren" authorityYear="1960" box="[387,524,1130,1156]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pontophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="4" pageNumber="423" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAB3D175FFC769D22E1BFDCBFB73" box="[387,524,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="423">Pontophoca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(table 1). We assign the femur to a new species, as it comes from the same geological time as the confidently referred material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D22D175FFC76B912EFBFB05FB53" baseAuthorityName="Alekseev" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[960,1218,1162,1188]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pontophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="4" pageNumber="423" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sarmatica">
<emphasis id="B90DEAB3D175FFC76B912EFBFB05FB53" box="[960,1218,1162,1188]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="423">Pontophoca sarmatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The comparison with material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D22D175FFC76A682EDAFD0BFB33" baseAuthorityName="Alekseev" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[569,716,1194,1220]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pontophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="4" pageNumber="423" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sarmatica">
<emphasis id="B90DEAB3D175FFC76A682EDAFD8EFB33" box="[569,585,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="423">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90DEAB3D175FFC76A082EDAFD0BFB33" box="[601,716,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="423">sarmatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is limited since the femur of 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D22D175FFC76C632EDAFB0FFB33" box="[1074,1224,1194,1220]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pontophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="4" pageNumber="423" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="jutlandica">
<emphasis id="B90DEAB3D175FFC76C632EDAFB85FB33" box="[1074,1090,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="423">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90DEAB3D175FFC76C032EDBFB0FFB33" box="[1106,1224,1194,1220]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="423">jutlandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks the medial part of the bone. However, the preserved section of the femur bears enough distinct characters to distinguish it as a new species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D22D175FFC76B782E9BFC75FAF3" authorityName="Mc Laren" authorityYear="1960" box="[809,946,1258,1284]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pontophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="4" pageNumber="423" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90DEAB3D175FFC76B782E9BFC75FAF3" box="[809,946,1258,1284]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="423">Pontophoca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. For detailed study and descriptions of humerus, femur, and other postcranial elements of 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D22D175FFC76B952F7BFB0EFAD3" baseAuthorityName="Alekseev" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[964,1225,1290,1316]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pontophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="4" pageNumber="423" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sarmatica">
<emphasis id="B90DEAB3D175FFC76B952F7BFB0EFAD3" box="[964,1225,1290,1316]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="423">Pontophoca sarmatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
